re key here.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.069996,0.11038,0.11795,0.11424,0.10187,0.087199,0.080685,0.07415,0.066429,0.067986,0.055777,0.053332],"unified_progress":[0.078119,0.082123,0.089845,0.099319,0.098545,0.092812,0.093491,0.087396,0.080024,0.079576,0.066129,0.052621]},{"section":6,"text":"They found HBsAg positive, which is the surface antigen of hepatitis B. That means he's infected with hepatitis B virus.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.061157,0.10103,0.1049,0.10375,0.099409,0.094444,0.088585,0.082849,0.074507,0.071376,0.061667,0.056325],"unified_progress":[0.068869,0.086356,0.093058,0.096096,0.097791,0.095967,0.093775,0.088591,0.080975,0.075633,0.06657,0.05632]},{"section":7,"text":"Then there's IgM anti-HBc.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.053615,0.097697,0.10631,0.10529,0.10036,0.094714,0.091505,0.085184,0.077808,0.071299,0.063368,0.052849],"unified_progress":[0.052278,0.086493,0.098038,0.10267,0.10601,0.10079,0.10239,0.087925,0.080784,0.071596,0.062423,0.048603]},{"section":8,"text":"The IgM core antibody is typically present in acute hepatitis B infections.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041566,0.081315,0.094772,0.1019,0.10346,0.099968,0.099086,0.091309,0.082829,0.078823,0.067838,0.057139],"unified_progress":[0.062277,0.074569,0.089561,0.097031,0.10188,0.10373,0.10381,0.091999,0.083453,0.076319,0.064553,0.050822]},{"section":9,"text":"In chronic infections, you usually see the IgG version instead.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036368,0.075583,0.089734,0.097975,0.10174,0.10098,0.1012,0.095037,0.087418,0.083832,0.071611,0.058518],"unified_progress":[0.065624,0.074223,0.087957,0.095453,0.099977,0.10132,0.10034,0.094054,0.085883,0.079865,0.065503,0.049802]},{"section":10,"text":"So the presence of IgM anti-HBc points towards an acute infection.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.044813,0.084009,0.094414,0.098159,0.096943,0.093676,0.092834,0.088251,0.083508,0.081353,0.072105,0.069935],"unified_progress":[0.050724,0.0746,0.087058,0.095954,0.098691,0.09734,0.09722,0.090758,0.086351,0.08115,0.074045,0.06611]},{"section":11,"text":"Also, HBeAg is positive.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.049258,0.091687,0.10079,0.10122,0.09818,0.09372,0.092451,0.087748,0.081645,0.076179,0.069206,0.057909],"unified_progress":[0.05025,0.082669,0.095048,0.10032,0.10443,0.09982,0.10325,0.089658,0.083054,0.074817,0.065813,0.050876]},{"section":12,"text":"HBeAg is a marker for high viral replication and infectivity.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040252,0.079925,0.092989,0.1003,0.10267,0.10063,0.09963,0.092424,0.083896,0.080836,0.068989,0.057458],"unified_progress":[0.051014,0.07374,0.089962,0.097338,0.10249,0.10588,0.10541,0.094157,0.085808,0.078588,0.065728,0.049887]},{"section":13,"text":"So putting this all together: acute hepatitis B.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.048272,0.08613,0.097736,0.10083,0.096527,0.08936,0.087454,0.083089,0.078801,0.082195,0.071639,0.077971],"unified_progress":[0.055052,0.068703,0.079285,0.09149,0.092653,0.09261,0.092355,0.091473,0.088341,0.088415,0.082295,0.07733]},{"section":14,"text":"The symptoms like jaundice, elevated liver enzymes, and the serology markers all fit.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036806,0.074166,0.08703,0.091979,0.09331,0.092377,0.093397,0.090813,0.089034,0.089308,0.084637,0.077143],"unified_progress":[0.041298,0.066645,0.077488,0.085662,0.091217,0.094738,0.09548,0.09584,0.095485,0.096442,0.087756,0.071948]},{"section":15,"text":"The conjugated bilirubin being high makes sense because in hepatitis, the liver's ability to process bilirubin is impaired, leading to conjugated (direct) hyperbilirubinemia.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":fa